articles.title: CFPB rule to save Americans $10 billion a year in late fees faces possible last-minute freeze - CNBC
articles.description: The credit card regulation is part of President Joe Biden's broader election-year war against what he deems junk fees.
articles.content:
A Consumer Financial Protection Bureau regulation that promised to save Americans billions of dollars in late fees on credit cards faces a last-ditch effort to stave off its implementation.
